[The incubation period of Lassa fever is known to be as long as 21 days.
But the chances of any of the air passengers being infected from her are
very small indeed. The people to watch are the hospital staff who had
contact with her blood & body fluids while she was still thought to have
malaria, before she was moved to the isolation ward. - Mod.JW
